wiki.summary: “HYAENA” is the introductory track to the highly-anticipated UTOPIA. In the track, Travis slyly, but quickly cruises over the topics of women, money, and fashion. Unlike the rest of the album, “HYAENA” primarily holds a Hip-Hop cadence which allows him to flow on the bouncy 90s-like beat as he samples both Funkadelic’s July 1971, “Maggot Brain,” and Gentle Giant’s September 1974, “Proclamation.” Throughout the track, Travis makes several references to other celebrities such as Kelsey Grammar and Chelsea Handler. Read more on Last.fm.
